SIMPLE: acephala
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Acephala
<hw>A*ceph"a*la</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <?/, adj. neut. pl., headless. See <er>Acephal</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>That division of the Mollusca which includes the
bivalve shells, like the clams and oysters; -- so called because they
have no evident head. Formerly the group included the Tunicata,
Brachiopoda, and sometimes the Bryozoa. See <er>Mollusca</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acephalan</ent>⟦br⟧
